<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Get started with the allocations service</h2>

<div class="govuk-grid-column">
  <div class="govuk-body">

    <p>You will be able to allocate prison offender managers to prisoners using the new allocations service.</p>

    <p>There are a few tasks that need to be completed before you can start making allocations.
      These need to be completed in the order that they are described in this guide.</p>

    <p>You will need to work together to complete the set-up.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><%=link_to "Task 1", "guidance_step1" %>: Senior Probation Officer / Head of Offender Management Unit (SPO/HoOMU)</li>
      <li><%=link_to "Task 2", "guidance_step2" %>: Local System Administrator</li>
      <li><%=link_to "Task 3", "guidance_step3" %>: Local System Administrator</li>
      <li><%=link_to "Task 4", "guidance_step4" %>: Senior Probation Officer / Head of Offender Management Unit (SPO/HoOMU) / Case admin</li>
      <li><%=link_to "Task 5", "guidance_step5" %>: Senior Probation Officer / Head of Offender Management Unit (SPO/HoOMU) / Case admin</li>
      <li><%=link_to "Task 6", "guidance_step6" %>: Senior Probation Officer / Head of Offender Management Unit (SPO/HoOMU)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>When you are set up, use Firefox to sign in to the service using your NOMIS ID
        and password at:
      <%= link_to "https://moic.service.justice.gov.uk", "https://moic.service.justice.gov.uk" %>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<br>
